Penalized regression

Linear regression \[ y_n = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{n,1} + \cdots + \beta_d x_{n,d} + \epsilon_n, \quad \epsilon_i \sim N(0,\sigma^2) \quad (n = 1,2,...,N) \] \[ \boldsymbol{y} = \boldsymbol{X}{\boldsymbol\beta} + {\boldsymbol\epsilon},\quad {\boldsymbol\epsilon}\sim N\left({\mathbf 0}_N, \sigma^2 \boldsymbol{I}_N\right) \]


  • \({\boldsymbol\beta}\) \[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta} = (\boldsymbol{X}^\top \boldsymbol{X})^{-1} \boldsymbol{X}^\top \boldsymbol{y} \]

    • \(\|\boldsymbol{y} - \boldsymbol{X}\boldsymbol\beta\|_2^2\)

    • : BLUE (best linear unbiased estimator)

    [] \({\cal L}_q\)-(norm): \(\,\,\boldsymbol{x} = (x_1, x_2, ..., x_N)^\top \in \mathbb{R}^N\) , \(\|\boldsymbol{x}\|_q = \left\{\sum_{n=1}^N \left|x_n\right|^q\right\}^{1/q}\). \[\begin{eqnarray*} & & (q = 1) \quad \|\boldsymbol{x}\|_1 = \sum_{n=1}^N \left|x_n\right|\\ & & (q = 2) \quad \|\boldsymbol{x}\|_2 = \left\{\sum_{n=1}^N x_n^2\right\}^{1/2} \equiv \left(\boldsymbol{x}^\top \boldsymbol{x}\right)^{1/2} \end{eqnarray*}\]


  • Issue 1 (Large \(d\), small \(N\))

    • \(X^\top X\)


  • Issue 2 (Bias-Variance trade-off)

    • : \({\sf MSE} = {\sf Bias}^2 + {\sf Variance}\) \[\begin{eqnarray*} \because \quad{\sf MSE} &=& {\sf E}\left[\left(\hat{\boldsymbol\theta} - \boldsymbol\theta\right)^2\right] = {\sf E}\left[\left\{\hat{\boldsymbol\theta} - {\sf E}(\hat{\boldsymbol\theta}) + {\sf E}(\hat{\boldsymbol\theta}) - \boldsymbol\theta\right\}^2\right] \\ &=& {\sf E}\left[\left\{\hat{\boldsymbol\theta} - {\sf E}(\hat{\boldsymbol\theta})\right\}^2\right] + \left\{{\sf E}(\hat{\boldsymbol\theta}) -\boldsymbol\theta\right\}^2 = {\sf Variance} + {\sf Bias}^2 \end{eqnarray*}\]

    • Bias . Variance .

    • Variance . Bias

    • (unbiasedness) ?


Ridge regression

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\sf ridge} = (\boldsymbol{X}^\top \boldsymbol{X} + \lambda \boldsymbol{I})^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\top\boldsymbol{y} \]

  • (\(\boldsymbol{0}\) ) shrink, bias

  • solution . \[ {\cal L}(\boldsymbol\beta) = \mbox{(Goodness of fit)} + \mbox{(Penalty)} = \| \boldsymbol{y} - \boldsymbol{X}{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 + \lambda \|{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 \]

  • (strictly) convex in \(\boldsymbol\beta\). . \[ \hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\sf ridge} =\arg\!\min_{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\left\{ \| \boldsymbol{y} - \boldsymbol{X}{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 + \lambda \|{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 \right\} \]

  • : \[ \text{To find } \boldsymbol{\beta} \text{ minimizing } \| \boldsymbol{y} - \boldsymbol{X}{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 \text{ subject to }\|{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2 \le R \text{ for some }R>0 \]


LASSO (least absolute shrinkage and selection operator)

  • ridge (\({\mathcal L}_1\)) \[ \hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\sf lasso} =\arg\!\min_{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\left\{ \| \boldsymbol{y} - \boldsymbol{X}{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 + \lambda \|{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_1 \right\} \]

  • \(\boldsymbol\beta\) convex

  • : \[ \text{To find }\boldsymbol{\beta} \text{ minimizing }\| \boldsymbol{y} - \boldsymbol{X}{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 \text{ subject to }\|{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_1 \le R \text{ for some }R>0 \]


\(\lambda\)

(cross-validation)

  • Leave-one-out \[ \textsf{CV}(\lambda) = \frac{1}{N}\sum_{i=1}^N\sum_{n\neq i}(y_n - \boldsymbol{x}_n^\top\boldsymbol\beta_{(-i)})^2 \]

(c.f.)


:

  • Variables: \((y, x_1, x_2, ..., x_{100})\)

  • DGP:

    • \(x_j\sim {\sf Uniform}(0, 1)\), \(j=1,2,...,100\)

    • \(y = 10 + 1\times x_1 + 2\times x_2 + ... + 5\times x_5 + \epsilon\), \(\epsilon\sim N(0, 0.25^2)\) (, \(x_6, x_7, ...x_{100}\) \(y\) )

  • \(n = 50\). .

library(glmnet)
## Loading required package: Matrix
## Loaded glmnet 4.1-10
set.seed(0)
n <- 50
p <- 100

sigma <- 0.25
beta <- c(1:5, rep(0, p - 5))

x <- cbind(matrix(runif(n*p), n, p))
y <- 10 + as.vector(x%*%beta) + sigma*rnorm(n)
fit <- glmnet(x, y)
plot(fit, xvar = "lambda", label = TRUE)

cvfit <- cv.glmnet(x, y)
plot(cvfit)

print(s <- cvfit$lambda.min)
## [1] 0.026306
print(log(s))
## [1] -3.637958
beta.hat <- coef(cvfit, s = "lambda.min")
print(round(drop(beta.hat), 4))

plot(y, pred.lasso, xlab = "Actual", ylab = "Predicted")
abline(0, 1, col = 2, lty = 2)

Elastic-net

  • \({\mathcal L}_1\)-norm \({\mathcal L}_2\)-norm \[ \frac{1 - \alpha}{2} \|\boldsymbol\beta \|_2^2 + \alpha \|\boldsymbol\beta\|_1 \]

  • \(\alpha = 0\) ridge regression, \(\alpha = 1\) lasso regression 

fit <- glmnet(x, y, alpha = .5)
plot(fit, xvar = "lambda", label = TRUE)

cvfit <- cv.glmnet(x, y, alpha = .5)
plot(cvfit)

print(s <- cvfit$lambda.min)
## [1] 0.03304186
print(log(s))
## [1] -3.40998
plot(y, pred.lasso, xlab = "Actual", ylab = "Predicted")
abline(0, 1, col = 2, lty = 2)
points(y, predict(fit, newx = x, s = s), col = "navy", pch = 19)

round(sqrt(mean((y - pred.lasso)^2)), 4)  # RMSE: LASSO
## [1] 0.1402
round(sqrt(mean((y - predict(fit, newx = x, s = s))^2)), 4) # RMSE: Elastic Net
## [1] 0.1135
